The paper focuses on using robots as a tool for investigating cognition, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses learning and human-like cognition, which are topics commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sensors and actuators in robots also relates to the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision in robotics, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
